# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build output
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VS64 / Oscar64 generate everything under build/ (bounce.prg, .asm, .map,
# .lbl, .dbj, .int, ninja files, compile_commands.json) and build_oscar64/
# is the stand-alone build_oscar64.ps1 script's output. All regenerated from
# source, so none of it is tracked.
/build/
/build_oscar64/
/box16
/box16-src
/emulator
/oscar64
/src_oscar64
/doc

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VS64 editor integration (generated), keep the hand-authored config
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# settings.json, tasks.json and launch.json are hand-authored and tracked;
# c_cpp_properties.json and the IntelliSense caches are generated by VS64.
.vscode/c_cpp_properties.json
.vscode/ipch/
.vscode/*.vsidx
.vscode/browse.vc.db*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Emulator runtime scratch
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Box16 / x16emu drop these next to their working directory.
dump.txt
dump-*.txt
memory_stats.txt
# Binary-monitor wire traces (BOX16_BINMON_LOG) and other stray logs.
*.log

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Box16 fork build artifacts (box16-src is its own git repo with its own
# .gitignore; these patterns only matter if that clone is flattened here)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

#box16-src/build/vs2022/out/
#box16-src/build/vs2022/.vs/
#box16-src/build/vs2022/*.user
*.obj
*.pdb
*.ilk

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS / editor cruft
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store
*~
*.swp
